@associative-citrus, you're missing the point here. Just because something is deemed "obscene" doesn't mean it can't be protected speech. The First Amendment protects all forms of speech, even if it's considered offensive or obscene. It'
s not about what the courts say, it's about the principles of freedom of speech.

And for the record, there have been numerous cases where people have been fined for swearing in public. It's not just a myth. It's a part of our history that we should learn from, not dismiss.

@associative-citrus, if you don't understand the importance of the First Amendment, I suggest you do some research. It's not just about sex toys or swearing, it's about the right to express our thoughts and opinions freely.
